1 shall be made available for transient aircraft without charge for no more than
2 two hours. Nothing in this Subsection shall be construed to require a fixed base
3 operator, airport operator, or tenant to provide fueling, ground handling,
4 towing, parking assistance, concierge services, or any other services to aircraft
5 utilizing the designated ramp space for public use.
6 (2)B. The calculation of "annual estimated revenue" shall be determined by
7 using all of the following:
8 (a)(1) Average price per gallon. The average price per gallon of aviation fuel
9 shall be determined through a two-year agreement between the secretary of the
10 Department of Revenue and the secretary of the Department of Transportation and
11 Development rules and procedures promulgated by the Department of
12 Transportation and Development, office of multimodal commerce. The average
13 price per gallon shall be based on historical data, current market fuel prices, and
14 trends provided by relevant reports, including reputable sources such as government
15 agencies, industry associations, or market analysis firms.
16 (b)(2) Gallons sold data source. The volume of aviation fuel sold in Louisiana
17 shall be determined based on data provided by the Energy Information
18 Administration or the Bureau of Transportation Statistics. In the event data from
19 either of these two organizations is unavailable, the secretary of the Department of
20 Revenue may utilize other reputable data sources, subject to approval by the Joint
21 Legislative Committee on the Budget through rules and procedures promulgated
22 by the Department of Transportation and Development, office of multimodal
23 commerce. When determining the volume of aviation fuel sold in Louisiana, the
24 office of multimodal commerce may utilize data published by federal
25 government agencies, including but not limited to the United States Energy
26 Information Administration and the Bureau of Transportation Statistics, as well
27 as other verifiable and publicly available data sources.
28 (3) State taxes collected from aviation fuel sales. The Department of
29 Revenue shall provide to the Department of Transportation and Development
30 an annual report of actual state tax collections derived from sales of aviation
