5 (c)(4) Sales tax rate. The sales tax rate applied in calculating the annual
6 estimated revenue shall be based on the current state sales tax rate in effect at the
7 time of the estimate. If the state sales tax rate changes during the fiscal year, the
8 annual estimated revenue shall be recalculated using the new sales tax rate.
9 (3) The secretary of the Department of Revenue shall submit the annual
10 estimated revenue to be derived from state taxes collected from purchases of aviation
11 fuel to the Revenue Estimating Conference within five calendar days of the annual
12 estimate being completed by the secretary.
13 C. The Revenue Estimating Conference shall utilize this estimation
14 formula and the rules and policies promulgated by the Department of
15 Transportation and Development, office of multimodal commerce, to develop
16 its annual estimate of aviation fuel taxes collected.
17 B. Reporting requirements. The secretary of the Department of Revenue shall
18 submit an annual report to the Joint Legislative Committee on the Budget no later
19 than March thirty-first of each year which contains the following information:
20 (1) The average price per gallon used in the calculation.
21 (2) The total gallons of aviation fuel sold in the state used in the calculation,
22 as reported by the Energy Information Administration or the Bureau of
23 Transportation Statistics.
24 (3) The sales tax rate applied in the calculation.
25 C. Legislative oversight. All agreements between the secretary of the
26 Department of Revenue and the secretary of the Department of Transportation and
27 Development required pursuant to the provisions of this Section related to the
28 calculation of the annual estimated revenue derived from sales of aviation fuel shall
29 be reviewed and approved by the Joint Legislative Committee on the Budget prior
30 to the agreement becoming binding between the parties.
